default4.1
default              
defaultAccess to Finance has been a huge concern for my Department for a number of years now and we have 
defaultraised
default this numerous times with Treasury Ministers over that time. I strongly believe this is acting as a constraint on our economic recovery and is a matter 
defaultthat needs to be addressed. The issue of Access to Finance has been extensively raised by the business community in consultations with Ministers and there are strong concerns that banks are not responding to the finance requirements of business. 
default&#xa0;
default4.2
default              
defaultMy D
defaultepartment and the previous Finance Minister met with the seven prominent banks operating in Northern Ireland, each of whom indicated that they did have money to lend, but cited depressed demand as an issue. Businesses on the other hand suggest that the ban
defaultks are operating in a manner where the cost and conditions attached to credit are prohibitive and I am sure that this is a major factor also – and one which could also be discouraging potential demand. This situation was recognised in March 2013 report by 
defaultthe Independent Economic Advisory Group (established by the Northern Ireland Enterprise Minister).
default&#xa0;
default4.3
default              
defaultWithout more detailed information on this from the banks it is difficult to assess the degree to which a lack of bank lending is impacting on the abilit
defaulty of businesses to access the finance they need to continue to trade and grow. The Executive does have an Access to Finance Strategy in place, led by DETI and Invest NI to assist with targeted inventions where appropriate. But the availability of bank lend
defaulting is central to this and is crucial for our economy and SMEs in particular.
default&#xa0;
default4.4
default              
defaultFurthermore, we have been disappointed at the implementation of the Better Business Finance Taskforce recommendations in Northern Ireland and in particular the uptake of the
default mentoring scheme and the independent appeals process. This is a matter I will be raising with the BBA Chief Executive Anthony Browne when I meet him in September.
