default7.1
default              
defaultI fully appreciate that banks need to examine their cost base as they seek to restructure their operations. However, I have been concerned at the branch closures announced in recent times, and in particular the impact of this in rural communities.
default 
defaultMy 
defaultpredecessor raised the issue of rural access with all four main banks here as part of his ongoing series of meetings with banks. And this is an issue I will continue to monitor and press local banks on in terms of their maintaining a strong rural presence 
default– particularly for elderly customers, who may not be as willing to use remote banking services and still require a face-to-face service. 
